We are continuously helping businesses integrate innovative ways for employers and employees to remotely fulfil their business roles. We know that working remotely can impact the productivity, management, teamwork, monitoring and operations of your company. The COVID-19 crisis is touching all aspects of society, including how we work and manage our staff. At such times, management solutions are no longer a luxury but rather a necessity for the survival of your business. In response, companies are asking their workforce to work remotely until the crisis abates. Do you need an immediate and long-term solution to monitor, manage and measure your employees work and performance form home? Can we put your mind at ease and help your company maintain productivity levels? At this time, don’t you need your office in your pocket to work remotely and safely, wherever you are? If your organisation doesn’t have a great deal of experience with remote working, there are a number of key aspects to consider about as you set up a remote working program. To help you mitigate the impact COVID-19 has on you and your organisation, and to implement a sustainable solution for the management of your workforce, we recommend Kadas – a Smart Management and Work-Flow application, available both on iOS and Android. Benefits of Kadas include: Cost saving – You don’t need to spend money developing a new system or pay for additional management and HR support. More productive – Time is not wasted, and remote work is structured so that losses are minimised. Flexibility – Keep to deadlines and client commitments with flexible scheduling and work from home support. Access to a wider pool of functionality – Business can continue as usual thanks to the features Kadas offers for your workers operating remotely. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-345009 size-large" src="https://mybroadband.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2020/03/Image-1-global-remote-working-640x360.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="360" srcset="